Page ³0. 3. Salinator: Cicero tells us that M. Livius Salinator commanded Tarentum when it was taken by Hannibal, buthe is undoubtedly in error. Livy gives the commander's name as M. Livius Macatus. The name Salinator was first given in ridicule, because M. Livius imposed a tax on salt, but it became the regular surname of the family.
